ltMsg":"Operation complete. \\"COBRA\\" captured. 2 associates detained. a hostage-taking event capability seized and destroyed.\\n\\nThe attack had been weeks in planning. Disruption at this stage prevents significant casualties.","confDelta":16,"budgetDelta":0,"dayReceived":311,"phaseFalseFlag":false,"phaseFalseFlagText":"","phaseFalseFlagPenalty":false,"followUpSpawned":false,"suspects":[\{"alias":"WOLF","role":"recruitment officer","confidence":"HIGH","isTarget":true,"eliminated":false\}],"selectedSuspectIdx":0,"invDays":2,"execDays":2,"baseBudget":4,"invDepts":["ANALYSIS","HUMINT","SIGINT","FIELD_OPS"],"execDepts":["FIELD_OPS","SPECIAL_OPS"],"opNarrative":"Field teams establish a tactical perimeter and move to neutralize the cell. HUMINT assets provide real-time target guidance while SIGINT intercepts communications. Special Operations holds in reserve for direct-action if the cell is armed. A simultaneous multi-point breach minimizes the risk of suspects fleeing.","initialReport":"Anonymous tip forwarded by Seattle metro police: suspicious activity consistent with a hostage-taking event preparation near a sports stadium.","fullReport":"INTELLIGENCE BRIEF \'97 OP JADE TIDE\\n\\nConfirmed: a hardline Islamist cell planning a hostage-taking event. Primary target: a sports stadium.\\n\\nHUMINT places cell leader (COBRA) in Seattle. Cell size: 2. Weapons acquisition believed complete.\\n\\nThreat level: CRITICAL. Time-sensitive. Recommend field neutralization.","successMsgs":["Cell neutralized. \{cell_size\} suspects detained. Materials seized. Planned attack against \{target\} prevented. No civilian casualties.\\n\\nPost-operation assessment confirms the cell was days from executing. HUMINT source proved reliable throughout.","Operation successful. \\"\{alias\}\\" and \{cell_size\} operatives apprehended. \{attack_type\} threat eliminated.\\n\\nFull debriefing of the cell leader is underway. Early indications suggest the cell had foreign logistical support.","Cell dismantled. Attack on \{target\} prevented. \{cell_size\} suspects in custody, materials secured.\\n\\nForensic teams are exploiting seized devices. Preliminary review suggests links to other domestic networks.","Operation complete. \\"\{alias\}\\" captured. \{cell_size\} associates detained. \{attack_type\} capability seized and destroyed.\\n\\nThe attack had been weeks in planning. Disruption at this stage prevents significant casualties."],"failureMsgs":["Operation blown. Cell received advance warning and dispersed. \{attack_type\} against \{target\} proceeded \'97 \{casualties\} casualties reported.\\n\\nThe source of the operational leak is under investigation. The cell leader \\"\{alias\}\\" remains at large.","Insufficient intelligence led to premature deployment. Field teams arrived post-event. \{casualties\} casualties. Cell leader \\"\{alias\}\\" remains at large.","Raid failed to locate cell. \\"\{alias\}\\" had already relocated. \{attack_type\} threat remains active.\\n\\n\{casualties\} casualties confirmed. Security review of the intelligence chain initiated.","Deployment compromised. Cell was warned. \\"\{alias\}\\" and associates scattered across the region.\\n\\nThe attack on \{target\} may still be active. Counter-terrorism units placed on heightened readiness."],"confSuccess":[10,18],"confFail":[-18,-30],"intelFields":[\{"key":"cell_location","label":"CELL LOCATION","value":"Approximate \'97 Seattle district, exact address pending","revealed":true\},\{"key":"cell_leader","label":"CELL LEADER IDENTITY","value":"Alias \\"COBRA\\" \'97 identity unverified, single-source","revealed":true\},\{"key":"attack_vector","label":"ATTACK METHOD","value":"a hostage-taking event \'97 delivery method confirmed by HUMINT","revealed":true\},\{"key":"attack_timeline","label":"OPERATIONAL TIMELINE","value":"Timeline unclear \'97 estimated within 10 days, low confidence","revealed":true\},\{"key":"arms_status","label":"WEAPONS STATUS","value":"Weapons acquisition complete \'97 ready to deploy","revealed":true\}],"intelBonus":true,"blown":false,"blownDaysLeft":0,"lastInvOutcome":"CRITICAL_SUCCESS","agencyJustification":"The source intelligence is derived from a classified SIGINT program unavailable to law enforcement counterparts. Executive authority under covert actions legislation permits direct action outside normal judicial channels. SAA maintains the operational deniability that a standard arrest cannot provide.","geoEventId":"GE11","attachedEliteIds":["EU2"],"agencySupport":[],"debriefHtml":"<div class=\\"db-wrap db-success\\"><div class=\\"db-toggle\\" onclick=\\"this.parentElement.classList.toggle('db-open')\\"><span class=\\"db-toggle-arrow\\">&#9654;</span><span class=\\"db-toggle-label\\">FULL OPERATIONAL DEBRIEF</span></div><div class=\\"db-body\\"><div class=\\"db-classification\\">TOP SECRET // SCI</div><div class=\\"db-title\\">AFTER-ACTION REPORT</div><div class=\\"db-subtitle\\">OP JADE TIDE \'97 OBJECTIVES ACHIEVED</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">DEPLOYED ASSETS</div><div class=\\"db-assets\\"><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">FIELD OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">field team \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SPECIAL OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">strike unit \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">HUMINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">handler \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SIGINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">intercept team \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">COUNTER-INTEL</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">officer \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row db-asset-elite\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">Element RAPTOR \u9733 </span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">Special Activities \'97 ELITE</span></div></div><div class=\\"db-meta\\">Budget committed: $2M \'b7 Pre-operation success assessment: 92%</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">OPERATION TIMELINE</div><div class=\\"db-day\\">14 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0700Z</span> STILETTO team assembled at forward staging area. Operational briefing conducted by FIELD OPS/SPECIAL OPS/HUMINT/SIGINT/COUNTER-INTEL command element. Weather assessment: Cold front moving through, variable conditions.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0805Z</span> Advance reconnaissance team deployed to Seattle. Confirmed target building visual. Building is a two-story residential structure.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1100Z</span> SIGINT intercept team established electronic surveillance perimeter. All target communications monitored in real-time. 5 active devices detected within the target structure.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1220Z</span> Surveillance team (SHADOW) reported 2 individuals observed entering the building over a 5-hour period. Pattern consistent with cell meeting.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1510Z</span> SPECIAL OPS element confirmed no counter-surveillance activity detected around the target area. Approach routes validated.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">15 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0430Z</span> Final intelligence update received. All 2 subjects confirmed present at target location. GO authorization received from Director.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0508Z</span> STILETTO assault element departed staging area. 4 vehicles in convoy. Radio silence enforced. ETA to target: 10 minutes.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0540Z</span> HUMINT source confirmed target disposition 55 minutes before H-hour, enabling final GO decision.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0549Z</span> SIGINT jammed hostile communications on the field commander's order during the final phase.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0559Z</span> Outer cordon established by FIELD OPS team. 6 positions covering all egress points. Local law enforcement discreetly diverted from the area of operations.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0608Z</span> Element RAPTOR led the primary assault element to breach point. Final equipment check completed. Weapons status confirmed.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0619Z</span> H-HOUR. Breach initiated via ladder assault to second-floor windows. No armed resistance. Two subjects were non-compliant but were subdued with non-lethal force. Entry to target achieved in under 10 seconds.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0624Z</span> Ground floor cleared. 2 subjects detained in the main room. Element RAPTOR personally secured \\"COBRA\\" who was found attempting to reach a weapon.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0630Z</span> Building fully cleared room by room. Total subjects detained: 2. No injuries to any personnel or subjects.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0638Z</span> Sensitive site exploitation team entered the building. Evidence recovery initiated. Items catalogued on-site include: hard drives containing operational planning documents. Additionally recovered: USB drives with encrypted files and correspondence.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0647Z</span> All 2 detainees processed, photographed, and biometrically registered. \\"COBRA\\" positively identified via facial recognition database match. Transport to secure holding facility arranged.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0659Z</span> Area of operations fully sanitized. No forensic evidence of agency involvement left on-site. STILETTO team and all support elements returned to base. Operation concluded.</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">ASSESSMENT</div><div class=\\"db-assessment\\">The operation against the a hardline Islamist cell cell in Seattle achieved all objectives. The planned a hostage-taking event against a sports stadium has been permanently disrupted. 2 operatives are in custody, including cell leader \\"COBRA\\". Intelligence exploitation of seized materials is the immediate priority \'97 hard drives containing operational planning documents are expected to yield significant insights into the wider network. Element RAPTOR performance during the breach phase was exemplary and directly contributed to the rapid, non-lethal subduing of the primary target. Operational security was maintained throughout. No media or public awareness of the operation has been detected. FIELD OPS/SPECIAL OPS/HUMINT/SIGINT/COUNTER-INTEL coordination rated EXCELLENT. Recommend commendation for STILETTO team leader.</div></div></div>","archivedDay":315\},\{"id":"M119","typeId":"FAVOR_AGENCY_RENDITION","codename":"THORN BASTION","threat":5,"label":"AGENCY FAVOR: RENDITION","category":"AGENCY FAVOR","location":"FOREIGN","city":"Addis Ababa","country":"Ethiopia","urgency":10,"urgencyLeft":2,"fillVars":\{"city":"Addis Ababa","country":"Ethiopia","codename":"THORN BASTION","urgency_days":"10","agency":"SAA","leaderTitle":"the President","bureau_name":"BUREAU","agency_name":"AGENCY","military_name":"DIA","alias":"BASILISK","rendition_role":"a senior network coordinator","agency_case":"a sanctions-busting procurement network takedown","diplomatic_constraint":"subject's country of origin would invoke diplomatic immunity","rendition_outcome":"Significant intelligence value extracted.","target_location_a":"BASILISK in Addis Ababa area \'97 AGENCY location unconfirmed at street level","capture_window_a":"Window estimated: 10 days \'97 AGENCY assessment","agency_support_fi":"AGENCY station support limited \'97 operation largely independent","diplomatic_field":"Diplomatic constraint: subject's country of origin would invoke diplomatic immunity \'97 details limited"\},"isMultiPhase":false,"status":"ARCHIVED","assignedInvDept":null,"invDaysLeft":0,"assignedBudget":4,"assignedExecDepts":["FOREIGN_OPS","SPECIAL_OPS","SIGINT","HUMINT","ANALYSIS"],"execDaysLeft":0,"successProb":92,"resultMsg":"Rendition operation complete. BASILISK in AGENCY custody. Significant intelligence value extracted.. Diplomatic constraint bypassed without incident.","confDelta":8,"budgetDelta":0,"dayReceived":305,"phaseFalseFlag":false,"phaseFalseFlagText":"","phaseFalseFlagPenalty":false,"followUpSpawned":false,"suspects":[],"selectedSuspectIdx":null,"invDays":4,"execDays":2,"baseBudget":8,"invDepts":["FOREIGN_OPS","HUMINT","SIGINT"],"execDepts":["FOREIGN_OPS","SPECIAL_OPS"],"opNarrative":"An AGENCY-supported snatch operation deploys through covert channels. Foreign Operations handles the capture while AGENCY personnel provide intelligence support from in-country station resources. The target is rendered through an AGENCY-managed exfil chain to a secure processing facility. SAA's role remains invisible \'97 AGENCY takes credit, and remembers the assist.","initialReport":"AGENCY has identified a high-value rendition target in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia. They need a capture team they can maintain deniability from. They're asking for us.","fullReport":"AGENCY RENDITION BRIEF \'97 OP THORN BASTION\\n\\nBASILISK (a senior network coordinator) \'97 Ethiopia rendition requested by AGENCY.\\n\\nCase: a sanctions-busting procurement network takedown. Constraint: subject's country of origin would invoke diplomatic immunity.\\n\\nAGENCY intel support provided. Our teams execute. Extraction via AGENCY-managed chain. Favor to be acknowledged.","successMsgs":["\{agency_name\} rendition favor complete. \{alias\} captured and delivered through \{agency_name\} chain. \{rendition_outcome\}. \{agency_name\} has confirmed receipt and noted the favor.","Rendition successful. \{alias\} (\{rendition_role\}) rendered from \{country\}. \{rendition_outcome\}. \{agency_name\} liaison acknowledged the assist \'97 relation improved.","Favor fulfilled. \{alias\} taken from \{city\} and passed to \{agency_name\} custody. \{rendition_outcome\}. \{agency_name\} will remember this.","\{agency_name\} favor complete. \{alias\} successfully rendered. \{rendition_outcome\}. \{agency_name\} relation strengthened. Back-channel acknowledgement received.","Rendition operation complete. \{alias\} in \{agency_name\} custody. \{rendition_outcome\}. Diplomatic constraint bypassed without incident.","\{agency_name\} favor fulfilled. \{alias\} \'97 \{rendition_role\} \'97 rendered and processed. \{rendition_outcome\}. \{agency_name\} relation payoff confirmed."],"failureMsgs":["Rendition failed. \{alias\} was not at the confirmed location. \{agency_name\} disappointed. Diplomatic window may have already closed.","Capture team compromised. \{alias\} fled before the operation could execute. \{country\} security forces responding. \{agency_name\} favor not fulfilled.","\{agency_name\} rendition blown. \{alias\} apparently had advance warning. Operation aborted. \{agency_name\} relation strained.","\{alias\} invoked diplomatic protection before capture could be executed. Legal complications triggered. \{agency_name\} favor incomplete.","Rendition window closed before team could act. \{alias\} departed \{country\}. \{agency_name\} favor not delivered.","Operation compromised by unknown source. \{alias\} warned and evacuated. \{agency_name\} disappointed. Investigation into leak ordered."],"confSuccess":[7,13],"confFail":[-8,-16],"intelFields":[\{"key":"target_location_a","label":"TARGET LOCATION","value":"BASILISK in Addis Ababa area \'97 AGENCY location unconfirmed at street level","revealed":true\},\{"key":"capture_window_a","label":"CAPTURE WINDOW","value":"Window estimated: 10 days \'97 AGENCY assessment","revealed":true\},\{"key":"agency_support_fi","label":"AGENCY SUPPORT","value":"AGENCY station support limited \'97 operation largely independent","revealed":true\},\{"key":"diplomatic_field","label":"DIPLOMATIC STATUS","value":"Diplomatic constraint: subject's country of origin would invoke diplomatic immunity \'97 details limited","revealed":false\}],"intelBonus":false,"blown":false,"blownDaysLeft":0,"lastInvOutcome":"PARTIAL","agencyJustification":"AGENCY requires a high-priority subject rendered and processed before diplomatic complications arise. Subject holds diplomatic-adjacent cover that legal proceedings cannot pierce. SAA covert rendition capability is the only instrument that can execute this capture within the operational window without triggering the diplomatic protections the subject would invoke.","favorOf":"AGENCY","favorAgencyName":"The Agency (CIA)","attachedEliteIds":["EU7"],"agencySupport":[],"debriefHtml":"<div class=\\"db-wrap db-success\\"><div class=\\"db-toggle\\" onclick=\\"this.parentElement.classList.toggle('db-open')\\"><span class=\\"db-toggle-arrow\\">&#9654;</span><span class=\\"db-toggle-label\\">FULL OPERATIONAL DEBRIEF</span></div><div class=\\"db-body\\"><div class=\\"db-classification\\">TOP SECRET // ORCON</div><div class=\\"db-title\\">AFTER-ACTION REPORT</div><div class=\\"db-subtitle\\">OP THORN BASTION \'97 OBJECTIVES ACHIEVED</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">DEPLOYED ASSETS</div><div class=\\"db-assets\\"><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">FOREIGN OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">cell \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SPECIAL OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">strike unit \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SIGINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">intercept team \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">HUMINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">handler \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">ANALYSIS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">desk \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row db-asset-elite\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">Station FREQUENCY \u9733 </span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">Signals Intelligence \'97 ELITE</span></div></div><div class=\\"db-meta\\">Budget committed: $4M \'b7 Pre-operation success assessment: 92%</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">OPERATION TIMELINE</div><div class=\\"db-day\\">14 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0645Z</span> The Agency (CIA) rendition request received. Target: BASILISK in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0805Z</span> FOREIGN OPS/SPECIAL OPS/SIGINT/HUMINT/ANALYSIS rendition team assembled. ECHO designated as acquisition lead. Target pattern of life reviewed \'97 acquisition window identified.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1130Z</span> Specialized equipment staged: false identity documents.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1450Z</span> Station FREQUENCY established overwatch from the operations center. Assigned: communications monitoring and early warning.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">16 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0315Z</span> Final confirmation: target following predicted routine. ECHO team deployed to acquisition point. Heavy cloud cover, no moonlight.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0354Z</span> Acquisition executed at the parking structure beneath target's office. Target intercepted exiting a vehicle. Secured within seconds.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0429Z</span> SIGINT provided real-time electronic surveillance \'97 scanning radio frequencies and phone networks in the target area.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0439Z</span> HUMINT source confirmed target disposition 30 minutes before H-hour, enabling final GO decision.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0445Z</span> ANALYSIS ran continuous risk modeling throughout the operation, flagging anomalies to the field commander.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0450Z</span> Counter-surveillance confirmed: acquisition was clean. Target's phone placed in Faraday bag.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0456Z</span> Target transported to a regional airstrip. Handoff to The Agency (CIA) completed. Chain of custody documented.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0517Z</span> All FOREIGN OPS/SPECIAL OPS/SIGINT/HUMINT/ANALYSIS elements extracted. Operational sites sanitized.</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">ASSESSMENT</div><div class=\\"db-assessment\\">Target BASILISK has been successfully rendered from Addis Ababa per The Agency (CIA) request. Acquisition was clean \'97 no witnesses, no compromise, no attribution. Station FREQUENCY provided continuous communications monitoring \'97 no alerts triggered during the operation. Target is now in The Agency (CIA) custody. This successful rendition strengthens the inter-agency relationship.</div></div></div>","archivedDay":315\},\{"id":"M118","typeId":"COUNTER_INTEL","codename":"BROKEN DAGGER","threat":2,"label":"COUNTER-INTEL","category":"INTERNAL SECURITY","location":"DOMESTIC","city":"Boston","country":"United States","urgency":28,"urgencyLeft":10,"fillVars":\{"city":"Boston","country":"United States","codename":"BROKEN DAGGER","urgency_days":"28","agency":"SAA","leaderTitle":"the President","bureau_name":"BUREAU","agency_name":"AGENCY","military_name":"DIA","suspect_count":"a small group of","suspect_profile":"a technical specialist","access_level":"SECRET / NOFORN","foreign_service":"a hostile foreign intelligence service","leaked_material":"classified assessments","duration":"3 years","suspect_profile_detail":"Honey-trap operation confirmed","dept_name":"analysis","suspect_identity":"a technical specialist \'97 identity confirmed, access logs corroborate","foreign_link":"Foreign beneficiary likely a hostile foreign intelligence service \'97 unconfirmed","compromised_material":"classified assessments confirmed compromised \'97 scope defined","access_pattern":"Suspicious access pattern observed \'97 statistical only, not conclusive","arrest_viability":"Evidence threshold met \'97 arrest authorized"\},"isMultiPhase":false,"status":"SUCCESS","assignedInvDept":null,"invDaysLeft":0,"assignedBudget":1,"assignedExecDepts":["COUNTER_INTEL","FIELD_OPS","HUMINT","SIGINT","ANALYSIS"],"execDaysLeft":0,"successProb":92,"resultMsg":"Internal threat neutralized. a technical specialist in custody. Leaked material accounted for. Network damage: limited.\\n\\nFull debrief will take weeks. Counter-Intelligence has recommended a security review of all personnel with similar access.","confDelta":11,"budgetDelta":0,"dayReceived":304,"phaseFalseFlag":false,"phaseFalseFlagText":"","phaseFalseFlagPenalty":false,"followUpSpawned":false,"suspects":[],"selectedSuspectIdx":null,"invDays":6,"execDays":1,"baseBudget":2,"invDepts":["ANALYSIS","COUNTER_INTEL","SIGINT"],"execDepts":["COUNTER_INTEL","FIELD_OPS"],"opNarrative":"Counter-Intelligence conducts a controlled burn \'97 feeding known-false intelligence into the network to identify the leak point. SIGINT monitors the subject's communications for the telltale signal. Once the mole is confirmed, Field Operations executes a quiet arrest before the subject can alert their handler or destroy evidence.","initialReport":"SIGINT flags encrypted outbound traffic from an internal terminal. Source and recipient unknown.","fullReport":"INTELLIGENCE BRIEF \'97 OP BROKEN DAGGER\\n\\nInternal investigation indicates a small group of individuals with access to compromised intelligence streams.\\n\\nPrimary suspect: a technical specialist. Access level: SECRET / NOFORN.\\n\\nForeign beneficiary: a hostile foreign intelligence service.\\n\\nRecommendation: Controlled surveillance and arrest operation.","successMsgs":["\{suspect_profile\} arrested. Partial confession obtained. \{foreign_service\} network partially rolled up. Damage assessment underway.\\n\\nThe controlled burn worked cleanly. Preliminary interrogation suggests the compromise was limited to one compartment.","Internal threat neutralized. \{suspect_profile\} in custody. Leaked material accounted for. Network damage: limited.\\n\\nFull debrief will take weeks. Counter-Intelligence has recommended a security review of all personnel with similar access.","Subject apprehended without incident. \{suspect_profile\} in custody. \{foreign_service\} handler unaware.\\n\\nDevice cloning complete. We now have a window into their communication protocols.","Arrest clean. \{suspect_profile\} cooperative under initial questioning. \{leaked_material\} compromise contained.\\n\\n\{foreign_service\} is now operating blind on the penetrated compartment."],"failureMsgs":["Surveillance operation blown. Suspect alerted and fled the country. \{foreign_service\} network intact. Damage unknown.\\n\\nThe subject had a pre-arranged exfiltration plan. A full damage assessment has been ordered.","Wrong suspect apprehended. Actual mole still active. \{foreign_service\} has now changed protocols.\\n\\nCounter-Intelligence is restarting the investigation. The mole knows we are looking.","Arrest attempted but subject invoked legal protections. Case may not hold up in closed proceedings.\\n\\nThe mole is aware. Exfil likely in progress. \{foreign_service\} has been alerted.","Controlled burn failed \'97 subject did not take the bait. Actual leak source remains unidentified.\\n\\n\{foreign_service\} continues to receive intelligence. Alternative investigation approach required."],"confSuccess":[6,12],"confFail":[-10,-18],"intelFields":[\{"key":"suspect_identity","label":"PRIMARY SUSPECT","value":"a technical specialist \'97 identity confirmed, access logs corroborate","revealed":true\},\{"key":"foreign_link","label":"FOREIGN BENEFICIARY","value":"Foreign beneficiary likely a hostile foreign intelligence service \'97 unconfirmed","revealed":true\},\{"key":"compromised_material","label":"LEAKED MATERIAL","value":"classified assessments confirmed compromised \'97 scope defined","revealed":true\},\{"key":"access_pattern","label":"ACCESS PATTERN","value":"Suspicious access pattern observed \'97 statistical only, not conclusive","revealed":true\},\{"key":"arrest_viability","label":"ARREST VIABILITY","value":"Evidence threshold met \'97 arrest authorized","revealed":true\}],"intelBonus":true,"blown":false,"blownDaysLeft":0,"lastInvOutcome":"CRITICAL_SUCCESS","agencyJustification":"This is a classified internal security matter. Bringing in external law enforcement would expose compartmented programs to uncontrolled legal proceedings. Counter-Intelligence directorate maintains sole jurisdiction over internal threat investigations under the SAA charter.","attachedEliteIds":["EU12"],"agencySupport":[],"_resultNew":true,"debriefHtml":"<div class=\\"db-wrap db-success\\"><div class=\\"db-toggle\\" onclick=\\"this.parentElement.classList.toggle('db-open')\\"><span class=\\"db-toggle-arrow\\">&#9654;</span><span class=\\"db-toggle-label\\">FULL OPERATIONAL DEBRIEF</span></div><div class=\\"db-body\\"><div class=\\"db-classification\\">TOP SECRET // ORCON</div><div class=\\"db-title\\">AFTER-ACTION REPORT</div><div class=\\"db-subtitle\\">OP BROKEN DAGGER \'97 OBJECTIVES ACHIEVED</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">DEPLOYED ASSETS</div><div class=\\"db-assets\\"><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">COUNTER-INTEL</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">officer \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">FIELD OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">field team \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">HUMINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">handler \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SIGINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">intercept team \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">ANALYSIS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">desk \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row db-asset-elite\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">Section BULWARK</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">Counter-Intelligence \'97 ELITE</span></div></div><div class=\\"db-meta\\">Budget committed: $1M \'b7 Pre-operation success assessment: 92%</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">OPERATION TIMELINE</div><div class=\\"db-day\\">23 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0615Z</span> Counter-intelligence investigation entered decisive phase. COUNTER-INTEL/FIELD OPS/HUMINT/SIGINT/ANALYSIS compiled findings from the preceding investigation period.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0930Z</span> Canary trap methodology deployed: 3 unique documents seeded through the suspect pool. Each variant contained traceable modifications invisible to the reader.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1135Z</span> Physical surveillance authorized on primary suspect. Section BULWARK assigned to the surveillance detail.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1200Z</span> Digital forensics team initiated covert monitoring of suspect's workstation access patterns, email traffic, and file transfers.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">24 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0145Z</span> Decision made to move to arrest. Evidence package reviewed by internal legal counsel: assessed as SUFFICIENT for prosecution and internal action.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0223Z</span> Arrest team assembled. SHADOW designated as lead. Location: suspect is currently at the cafeteria.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0240Z</span> HUMINT source confirmed target disposition 45 minutes before H-hour, enabling final GO decision.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0244Z</span> SIGINT provided real-time electronic surveillance \'97 scanning radio frequencies and phone networks in the target area.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0251Z</span> ANALYSIS provided real-time threat assessment and target pattern analysis from the operations center.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0254Z</span> Suspect approached by SHADOW team. Suspect attempted to destroy their phone by smashing it \'97 device partially recovered.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0303Z</span> Suspect's workspace secured and sealed. Digital forensics team began imaging all devices. Personal effects catalogued. An unauthorized encrypted USB drive was recovered from the suspect's bag.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0308Z</span> Suspect's residence searched under judicial authority. Recovery included: USB drives with encrypted files and correspondence.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0317Z</span> Suspect transferred to secure detention facility. Formal interrogation scheduled. Damage assessment team mobilized to review all programs and operations the suspect had access to.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0330Z</span> Full access audit initiated: suspect held SECRET clearance with broad access to operational databases. Scope of potential compromise: SIGNIFICANT.</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">ASSESSMENT</div><div class=\\"db-assessment\\">The counter-intelligence investigation has successfully identified and neutralized an insider threat. The suspect had been passing classified information to a foreign government via an intermediary network for an estimated 5 months. COUNTER-INTEL officer, FIELD OPS field team, HUMINT handler, SIGINT intercept team, ANALYSIS desk conducted the investigation with appropriate discretion, preventing the suspect from learning of the inquiry until the arrest. Section BULWARK was instrumental during the surveillance phase, documenting critical meetings that established the suspect's guilt. Damage assessment is the immediate priority. All operations and sources the suspect had access to must be evaluated for compromise. Preliminary estimates suggest 16 intelligence products may have been passed to the adversary. The suspect is in custody and formal interrogation will commence within 24 hours.</div></div></div>"\},\{"id":"M117","typeId":"NETWORK_EXPANSION","codename":"SHADOW STORM","threat":3,"label":"NETWORK EXPANSION","category":"INTELLIGENCE OPERATIONS","location":"FOREIGN","city":"Amsterdam","country":"Netherlands","urgency":20,"urgencyLeft":10,"fillVars":\{"city":"Amsterdam","country":"Netherlands","codename":"SHADOW STORM","urgency_days":"20","agency":"SAA","leaderTitle":"the President","bureau_name":"BUREAU","agency_name":"AGENCY","military_name":"DIA","theater_name":"Western Europe","cover_status":"Cover identity prepared \'97 final documentation pending","recruitment_targets":"Three viable candidates identified \'97 motivation and access profiles characterized","local_ci_assessment":"Local CI posture MODERATE \'97 additional precautions required"\},"isMultiPhase":false,"status":"ARCHIVED","assignedInvDept":null,"invDaysLeft":0,"assignedBudget":8,"assignedExecDepts":["FOREIGN_OPS","HUMINT","SIGINT","ANALYSIS"],"execDaysLeft":0,"successProb":92,"resultMsg":"Network expansion achieved. New collection streams active in Netherlands. Safe house chain and exfiltration protocols in place. Coverage rating: ADEQUATE.","confDelta":3,"budgetDelta":0,"dayReceived":299,"phaseFalseFlag":false,"phaseFalseFlagText":"","phaseFalseFlagPenalty":false,"followUpSpawned":false,"suspects":[],"selectedSuspectIdx":null,"invDays":3,"execDays":7,"baseBudget":13,"invDepts":["ANALYSIS","HUMINT","SIGINT"],"execDepts":["FOREIGN_OPS","HUMINT"],"opNarrative":"Foreign Operations establishes a cover platform in Amsterdam. HUMINT handlers identify and develop potential sources within the local intelligence, military, and political establishments. The recruitment cycle \'97 spot, assess, develop, recruit \'97 is executed methodically over the operational window. Supporting infrastructure (safe houses, dead drops, communications protocols) is established in parallel.","initialReport":"Western Europe theater coverage deficient. Asset recruitment operation in Amsterdam, Netherlands will expand intelligence collection capability.","fullReport":"NETWORK EXPANSION BRIEF \'97 OP SHADOW STORM\\n\\nTheater: Western Europe. Location: Amsterdam, Netherlands.\\n\\nCurrent intelligence coverage in this area is insufficient. This operation will develop new sources within local power structures and establish supporting clandestine infrastructure.\\n\\nRecommended approach: gradual recruitment through established cover, supported by SIGINT targeting.","successMsgs":["Network established. Three new sources recruited in \{city\}. Collection infrastructure operational. \{theater_name\} theater coverage significantly improved.","Operation complete. Source network in \{country\} is now active and producing. Dead-drop chain and secure communications established. Theater coverage upgraded.","Recruitment cycle successful. Multiple assets now reporting from \{city\}. Cover platforms secure. \{theater_name\} intelligence capability enhanced.","Network expansion achieved. New collection streams active in \{country\}. Safe house chain and exfiltration protocols in place. Coverage rating: ADEQUATE."],"failureMsgs":["Cover platform compromised in \{city\}. Lead recruiter identified by local CI. All assets burned. Network expansion failed.","Operation blown. Local security services arrested the principal agent in \{country\}. Recruitment program terminated. Coverage gap remains.","Source development unsuccessful. Target environment in \{city\} proved hostile. No viable assets recruited. \{theater_name\} coverage unchanged.","Cover story collapsed. Two officers detained briefly before diplomatic extraction. Network infrastructure abandoned. Operation failed."],"confSuccess":[2,5],"confFail":[-3,-6],"intelFields":[\{"key":"cover_status","label":"COVER PLATFORM","value":"Cover identity prepared \'97 final documentation pending","revealed":true\},\{"key":"recruitment_targets","label":"RECRUITMENT TARGETS","value":"Three viable candidates identified \'97 motivation and access profiles characterized","revealed":true\},\{"key":"local_ci_assessment","label":"LOCAL CI POSTURE","value":"Local CI posture MODERATE \'97 additional precautions required","revealed":true\}],"intelBonus":false,"blown":false,"blownDaysLeft":0,"lastInvOutcome":"PARTIAL","agencyJustification":"SAA requires expanded human intelligence coverage in the Western Europe theater. Current network penetration is insufficient for adequate threat detection and operational support. Authorization is requested for a clandestine recruitment and infrastructure development program in Amsterdam, Netherlands.","networkTheaterId":"WESTERN_EUROPE","attachedEliteIds":["EU13","EU3"],"agencySupport":[],"debriefHtml":"<div class=\\"db-wrap db-success\\"><div class=\\"db-toggle\\" onclick=\\"this.parentElement.classList.toggle('db-open')\\"><span class=\\"db-toggle-arrow\\">&#9654;</span><span class=\\"db-toggle-label\\">FULL OPERATIONAL DEBRIEF</span></div><div class=\\"db-body\\"><div class=\\"db-classification\\">TOP SECRET // ORCON</div><div class=\\"db-title\\">AFTER-ACTION REPORT</div><div class=\\"db-subtitle\\">OP SHADOW STORM \'97 OBJECTIVES ACHIEVED</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">DEPLOYED ASSETS</div><div class=\\"db-assets\\"><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">FOREIGN OPS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">cell \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">HUMINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">handler \'97 PRIMARY</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">SIGINT</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">intercept team \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">ANALYSIS</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">desk \'97 SUPPORT</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row db-asset-elite\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">Cell PASSAGE</span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">Foreign Operations \'97 ELITE</span></div><div class=\\"db-asset-row db-asset-elite\\"><span class=\\"db-asset-dept\\">Desk QUILL \u9733 </span><span class=\\"db-asset-type\\">Analysis Bureau \'97 ELITE</span></div></div><div class=\\"db-meta\\">Budget committed: $8M \'b7 Pre-operation success assessment: 92%</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">OPERATION TIMELINE</div><div class=\\"db-day\\">12 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0530Z</span> FOREIGN OPS/HUMINT/SIGINT/ANALYSIS advance team arrived in Amsterdam under cover. Cover platform established: a cultural exchange program.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0750Z</span> Initial area familiarization. Case officers mapped the local security environment \'97 police presence, surveillance cameras, counter-intelligence patterns.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0815Z</span> Target environment assessment completed. Target-rich environment. Multiple potential recruitment candidates identified through social mapping.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1020Z</span> Cell PASSAGE embedded with the advance team. Assumed role: technical operations specialist.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">14 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0910Z</span> Source development phase initiated. Primary recruitment target identified: a port authority official controlling customs records. Designated ASSET-1.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1105Z</span> Initial contact with ASSET-1 via a mutual acquaintance in the business community. Assessment: ideologically sympathetic \'97 promising.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1350Z</span> Parallel spotting. Second potential source identified: a telecommunications engineer with network access. Designated ASSET-2. Approached through different case officer to compartmentalize.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1450Z</span> SIGINT sweep detected no technical surveillance on team communications.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">19 NOV 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0650Z</span> ASSET-1 recruitment pitch delivered. Method: exploitation of a compromising personal situation. Result: ACCEPTED after negotiation. Terms: regular financial compensation and eventual resettlement guarantee.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0945Z</span> Additional recruitment: ASSET-2 successfully recruited via mutual contact introduction through an existing low-level asset. Total active sources: 4.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1225Z</span> Clandestine infrastructure established: a secure covert communications channel using encrypted messaging. Additionally: dead-drop sites at 4 locations across the city.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1530Z</span> First intelligence product received from ASSET-1. Content: internal government communications regarding military deployments.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1730Z</span> Cell PASSAGE conducted the primary recruitment meeting. Rapport was exceptional \'97 source expressed full confidence in the handler.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1825Z</span> Exfiltration of case officers commenced. Cover platform will remain operational for ongoing source handling. Station handover to permanent resident officer initiated.</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">ASSESSMENT</div><div class=\\"db-assessment\\">Network expansion operation in Amsterdam, Netherlands (Western Europe theater) achieved all objectives. 4 human intelligence sources successfully recruited and producing. Cover platform operational and sustainable. Clandestine infrastructure \'97 including dead drops, safe houses, and secure communications \'97 established and tested. Cell PASSAGE was instrumental in the recruitment phase, personally handling the primary source pitch. Intelligence products already received include reporting on military dispositions. Western Europe theater intelligence coverage has been significantly upgraded. FOREIGN OPS/HUMINT/SIGINT/ANALYSIS performance rated EXCEPTIONAL.</div></div></div>","archivedDay":318\},\{"id":"M116","typeId":"ORG_INFILTRATION","codename":"AMBER SERPENT","threat":4,"label":"ORG INFILTRATION","category":"NETWORK PENETRATION","location":"FOREIGN","city":"Tripoli","country":"Libya","urgency":45,"urgencyLeft":31,"fillVars":\{"city":"Tripoli","country":"Libya","codename":"AMBER SERPENT","urgency_days":"45","agency":"SAA","leaderTitle":"the President","bureau_name":"BUREAU","agency_name":"AGENCY","military_name":"DIA","org_name":"THE SILVER ORCHID"\},"isMultiPhase":true,"status":"EXECUTING","assignedInvDept":null,"invDaysLeft":0,"assignedBudget":3,"assignedExecDepts":["HUMINT","SIGINT","FOREIGN_OPS","ANALYSIS"],"execDaysLeft":3,"successProb":92,"resultMsg":"","confDelta":0,"budgetDelta":0,"dayReceived":296,"phaseFalseFlag":false,"phaseFalseFlagText":"","phaseFalseFlagPenalty":false,"followUpSpawned":false,"suspects":[],"selectedSuspectIdx":null,"phases":[\{"id":"APPROACH","name":"Phase 1: Approach & Recruitment","shortName":"APPROACH","invDaysRange":[4,7],"invDepts":["HUMINT","ANALYSIS",