n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0520Z</span> Final surveillance pass of target location. Target confirmed present. Security detail observed: 1 armed individuals in a rotating patrol.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0825Z</span> SIGINT confirmed target's phone active at location. Voice identification positive. Target is conducting no calls \'97 device on standby.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1110Z</span> Approach route finalized. Primary: foot infiltration through adjacent property. Alternate route briefed in case of compromise.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">1210Z</span> Weather forecast for execution window: Light rain, intermittent. Assessment: ACCEPTABLE.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-day\\">18 OCT 2025</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0115Z</span> H-HOUR MINUS 60. Final intelligence update: target confirmed at location. No unusual activity detected. GO authorization confirmed.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0142Z</span> HAMMER assault element departed staging area. Light rain, intermittent. All teams moving to assigned positions.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0200Z</span> ANALYSIS desk maintained the common operating picture \'97 fusing HUMINT, SIGINT, and field reporting.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0208Z</span> HUMINT source confirmed target disposition 89 minutes before H-hour, enabling final GO decision.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0213Z</span> SIGINT intercept team monitored all target communications throughout the operation.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0218Z</span> Outer security perimeter established. 3 escape routes blocked by SPECIAL OPS elements.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0230Z</span> H-HOUR. Breach initiated via diversionary blast on east wall with primary entry from the west. Station FREQUENCY confirmed all sensor feeds active \'97 providing overwatch from the operations center. Security detail engaged and suppressed.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0233Z</span> Target located in a meeting room with associates. Minimal resistance. One subject attempted to flee on foot but was tackled by perimeter team.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0244Z</span> Target positively identified via fingerprint match. Identity confirmed: HAMMER.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0248Z</span> Target sedated per medical protocol and transferred to prepared transport vehicle. Cover story for disappearance will be a staged domestic dispute.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0255Z</span> Site exploitation team entered. 12 minutes of rapid evidence collection. Items recovered: surveillance photography of 4 potential targets.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0306Z</span> Extraction commenced via ground vehicle convoy using three armored SUVs. All teams departed area of operations. No pursuit detected. HAMMER confirmed clean extraction.</div>\\n<div class=\\"db-event\\"><span class=\\"db-time\\">0324Z</span> Target delivered to agency black site. Chain of custody documented. All FIELD OPS/SPECIAL OPS/ANALYSIS/HUMINT/SIGINT elements accounted for and RTB.</div><div class=\\"db-section-title\\">ASSESSMENT</div><div class=\\"db-assessment\\">High-value target HAMMER has been successfully acquired in Seattle. The operation was executed by FIELD OPS field team, SPECIAL OPS strike unit, ANALYSIS desk, HUMINT handler, SIGINT intercept team with elite asset Station FREQUENCY attached. Total operation time from breach to extraction: approximately 32 minutes. The target is now in secure custody and initial tactical questioning has begun. Seized materials from the target location are undergoing exploitat